  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The best  way to deal with markdown where you want to keep the attributes is:\r\n\r\n1. escapeHTML: false\r\n2. run your markdown changing\r\n3. escape again to prevent XSS, depending on which tags you want to allow\r\n\r\nA  fairly similar mechanism is done for the yarn website (however that one is done with React InstantSearch) https://github.com/yarnpkg/website/blob/master/js/src/lib/util.js#L196\r\n\r\nAt the end, we found that while trying to do this, we often broke markdown tags by highlighting, so more complex logic is necessary for that, which should also be done with escapeHTML false.\r\n\r\nYou can see an example html escape we use here https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/develop/src/lib/utils/escape.ts",
